                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13175083" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 22 Dec 2011 21:38:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This feels clunky to me.  Wouldn&apos;t it be better to have both CFS and non-CFS indexes provide the same API so we can do it polymorphically w/ a single loop?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13175133" author="tjake" created="Thu, 22 Dec 2011 23:04:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;attached a different approach.  The polymorphic approach would still be clunky because it includes self, so you need to get self + indexes.  latest patch seems more readable.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
